Zambian Peacekeepers Shot in Disputed Sudan Region

-- B y   M a r a m   M a z e n
-- 
2011-05-11T17:10:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-11/zambian-peacekeepers-shot-in-disputed-sudan-region-correct-.html
(Corrects spelling of region in story published May 10.)  Four peacekeepers were shot by
unidentified gunmen in the disputed Sudanese region of Abyei,
the  United Nations  said.  The troops, who are Zambian nationals, were wounded in the
attack today that took place in Goli, about 25 kilometers north
of Abyei town, according to an e-mailed statement.  At least 14 people were killed last week in clashes in
Abyei, which is claimed by both northern and  Southern Sudan , the
UN said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Maram Mazen in Khartoum at 
 mmazen@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Emily Bowers at 
 ebowers1@bloomberg.net  